VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com

# === CLOUDFLARE PAGES ===
# Per il deploy, impostare queste variabili nel dashboard Cloudflare Pages:
# - Production: Pages → NetFlow → Settings → Environment Variables
# - Preview: Pages → NetFlow → Settings → Environment Variables (same values)
#
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
# VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID  (solo se riattivato)

# === SERVER-SIDE VARIABLES (for supabase/config.toml) ===
# Uncomment and set these for local development email
# SUPABASE_AUTH_SMTP_HOST=smtp.sendgrid.net
# SUPABASE_AUTH_SMTP_PORT=587
# SUPABASE_AUTH_SMTP_USER=apikey
# SUPABASE_AUTH_SMTP_PASS=your-sendgrid-api-key
# SUPABASE_AUTH_SMTP_SENDER=noreply@netflow.app

# === INSTRUCTIONS ===
# 1. Create a Supabase project at https://supabase.com
# 2. Copy the Project URL -> VITE_SUPABASE_URL
# 3. Copy the anon public key -> VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
# 4. Enable Google OAuth in Supabase Auth -> settings -> VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID
# 5. Run: npx supabase link --project-ref your-project-ref
# 6. Run: npx supabase db push
# 7. Deploy su Cloudflare Pages: npm run build -> carica dist/
